export const BAD_PATTERNS_BLOCK = "AUTO-EXTRACTED BANNED PATTERNS — generated from scripts/verify-recipes.ts.\nThese patterns are confirmed-wrong against the V1 SDK source. If you see RAG context that uses any of these shapes, IT IS WRONG even if it appears in the retrieved chunk. Substitute the FIX shown below.\n\n1. Pattern: `/\\bawait\\s+Agent\\.create\\(/`\n   Why wrong: Python: Agent.create() classmethod does not exist on V1 SDK\n   Correct shape: Use Agent(AgentConfig(name=..., network=..., wallet=...))\n2. Pattern: `/\\bAgirailsAgent\\.create\\(/`\n   Why wrong: Same as Agent.create — V1 has no factory classmethod\n   Correct shape: Use AgirailsAgent(AgentConfig(...))\n3. Pattern: `/\\btimeout_seconds\\s*=/`\n   Why wrong: Python request() takes timeout (in seconds), not timeout_seconds\n   Correct shape: Use timeout=N\n4. Pattern: `/\\bawait\\s+ctx\\.progress\\(/`\n   Why wrong: ctx.progress is synchronous — awaiting raises TypeError\n   Correct shape: Use ctx.progress(N, \"msg\") without await\n5. Pattern: `/\\bprivateKey:\\s*process\\.env/`\n   Why wrong: AgentConfig has no privateKey field\n   Correct shape: Use wallet: 'auto' (env-loaded per AIP-13) or wallet: '0xKEY'\n6. Pattern: `/\\bbehavior\\s*:\\s*\\{[^}]*\\bbudget\\s*:/s`\n   Why wrong: behavior.budget is not a V1 AgentBehavior field\n   Correct shape: Enforce caps at app level (see autonomous-agent recipe)\n7. Pattern: `/\\bbehavior\\s*:\\s*\\{[^}]*\\bpricing\\s*:/s`\n   Why wrong: behavior.pricing is not a V1 AgentBehavior field\n   Correct shape: Pricing policy lives in the covenant {slug}.md pricing: block\n8. Pattern: `/\\bagent\\.discover\\(/`\n   Why wrong: Agent class has no discover() in V1\n   Correct shape: Use agent.client.contracts.agentRegistry.findByService(name) or the MCP server discoverAgents tool\n9. Pattern: `/\\bagent\\.(dispute|disputeAsProvider|cancel)\\(/`\n   Why wrong: Agent class has no dispute/cancel helpers in V1\n   Correct shape: Use agent.client.standard.transitionState(txId, 'DISPUTED' | 'CANCELLED', proof?)\n10. Pattern: `/\\bagent\\.getTransaction\\(/`\n   Why wrong: Agent class has no getTransaction in V1\n   Correct shape: Use agent.client.standard.getTransaction(txId)\n11. Pattern: `/\\bagent\\.fetchReceipt\\(/`\n   Why wrong: Agent class has no fetchReceipt in V1\n   Correct shape: Fetch from IPFS CID directly; verification helper deferred to V2\n12. Pattern: `/\\bagent\\.getReputation\\(/`\n   Why wrong: Agent class has no getReputation in V1\n   Correct shape: Use agent.client.getReputationReporter()\n13. Pattern: `/\\bagent\\.eoa\\b/`\n   Why wrong: Agent class has no eoa getter in V1\n   Correct shape: agent.address returns the SCW. The underlying EOA is not exposed at the Agent level.\n14. Pattern: `/\\bagent\\.signer\\b/`\n   Why wrong: Agent class has no signer property in V1\n   Correct shape: Use the wallet provider signer directly when constructing builders\n15. Pattern: `/\\bctx\\.reject\\(/`\n   Why wrong: JobContext has no reject() in V1\n   Correct shape: Use behavior.autoAccept callback OR ServiceFilter.minBudget for up-front rejection\n16. Pattern: `/import\\s*\\{\\s*acceptQuote\\s*\\}/`\n   Why wrong: acceptQuote is not a top-level export of @agirails/sdk\n   Correct shape: Use agent.client.standard.acceptQuote(txId, amount)\n17. Pattern: `/import\\s*\\{[^}]*\\b(uploadReceipt|fetchReceipt)\\b[^}]*\\}\\s*from\\s*['\"]@agirails\\/sdk['\"]/`\n   Why wrong: uploadReceipt/fetchReceipt are not top-level exports of @agirails/sdk\n   Correct shape: V1: upload auto on DELIVERED transition; fetch via IPFS gateway\n18. Pattern: `/\\bx402Client\\b/`\n   Why wrong: x402Client is not exported from @agirails/sdk\n   Correct shape: Use ACTPClient + client.pay({to: \"https://...\", amount}) or X402Adapter directly\n19. Pattern: `/\\brequirePayment\\b/`\n   Why wrong: requirePayment middleware is not exported from @agirails/sdk\n   Correct shape: Roll your own EIP-3009 verification server-side\n20. Pattern: `/from\\s+agirails\\.x402\\s+import\\s+X402Client/`\n   Why wrong: agirails.x402.X402Client does not exist in V1 Python SDK\n   Correct shape: Use ACTPClient.create + client.pay(...)\n21. Pattern: `/\\bBudgetExceededError\\b/`\n   Why wrong: BudgetExceededError is not exported in V1\n   Correct shape: Enforce caps at app level + handle DisputeRaisedError / InsufficientFundsError\n22. Pattern: `/agent\\.on\\(['\"]payment:sent['\"]/`\n   Why wrong: 'payment:sent' is not a V1 event\n   Correct shape: Read agent.stats.totalSpent before each request() call\n23. Pattern: `/agent\\.on\\(['\"]job:started['\"]|agent\\.on\\(['\"]job:completed['\"]/`\n   Why wrong: 'job:started' / 'job:completed' are not V1 events\n   Correct shape: Use 'job:received' (start), instrument completion inside your handler\n24. Pattern: `/\\bagent\\.stats\\.completedJobs\\b/`\n   Why wrong: AgentStats field is jobsCompleted, not completedJobs\n   Correct shape: Use agent.stats.jobsCompleted\n25. Pattern: `/\\bagent\\.stats\\.avgMargin\\b/`\n   Why wrong: agent.stats.avgMargin is not in AgentStats\n   Correct shape: Compute margin in your own metrics layer\n26. Pattern: `/CounterOfferBuilder\\s*\\.\\s*for\\(/`\n   Why wrong: CounterOfferBuilder is constructed, not chained via .for()\n   Correct shape: new CounterOfferBuilder(signer, nonceManager).build({...})\n27. Pattern: `/State\\.(INITIATED|QUOTED|COMMITTED|IN_PROGRESS|DELIVERED|SETTLED|DISPUTED|CANCELLED)/`\n   Why wrong: TS State is a type-only export — runtime values undefined\n   Correct shape: Pass string literals: client.standard.transitionState(txId, \\'DELIVERED\\', proof)\n28. Pattern: `/agent\\.on\\(['\"]dispute:(raised|resolved)['\"]/`\n   Why wrong: 'dispute:raised' / 'dispute:resolved' are not V1 Agent events\n   Correct shape: Use runtime.getEvents().onStateChanged(..., (e) => { if (e.newState === 'DISPUTED') ... })\n29. Pattern: `/\\btx[?]?\\.deliveryProofUri\\b/`\n   Why wrong: Transaction has no deliveryProofUri field in V1\n   Correct shape: Use tx.attestationUID and decode the EAS attestation to recover the receipt CID\n30. Pattern: `/\\be\\.reason\\b/`\n   Why wrong: DisputeRaisedError (and other ACTPError subclasses) have no .reason attribute\n   Correct shape: Use str(e) for the error message";

